Considering such a narrative, it *does* offer several opportunities to dismantle tiresome tropes. {Actually, {boldly, {carefully, {distinctly, {elegantly, {formidably, {gracefully, {honestly, {intelligently, {justifiably, {keenly, {logically, {methodically, {naturally, {objectively, {precisely, {quietly, {rationally, {scientifically, {thoroughly, {unreservedly, {vividly, {wisely, {xenophobically, {youthfully, {zealously}}}}}}}}}}}}}}}}}}}}}}}}}}}}}} The most obvious is the “damsel in distress” trope. Usually, the protagonist *rescues* the love interest. Here, he’s rescuing a *copy*. It’s not a rescue, it’s…a re-introduction. A forced intimacy. 

